    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "Promote adoption of safe behaviors among most-at-risk populations (MARPS) (labor migrants\r\n    and their spouses, IDUs, and MSM) through increased access and availability of prevention\r\n    programs;\r\n    Expand access and coverage of quality HIV testing and counseling, as well as diagnosis and\r\n    treatment of sexually transmitted infections (STls);\r\n    Strengthen health services capacity to provide quality care and treatment for PLHA;\r\n    Increase access to quality community-based care and treatment for PLHA; and\r\n    Build the capacity of the Government of Nepal (GON) and civil society to manage and\r\n    implement HIV/AIDS activities."
      },
